{
  "texts": [
    "Figure 5 showcases the improvement of including an artifact detector (Classifier A) before passing data through Classifier S. Indeed, the improvement ranged from 58% to 96% with the standard scaling method having the best performance.",
    "Additionally, normal EEG data have only a small chance (0.04%) of being incorrectly classified as seizures using this standard scaling method.",
    "These results quantitatively confirm that using an artifact detector before a seizure detection model allows to significantly reduce false alarms.",
    "A question left unanswered is: does the artifact detector affect the sensitivity of the seizure detector?",
    "In other words, does the artifact detector prevent some seizures from being classified and detected?"
  ]
}